{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Use Australian English|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox rugby league biography |name = Frank Benning |fullname = Herbert Francis Benning |birth_date = 1907 |birth_place = [[Gunnedah, New South Wales]] |death_date = 8 February 1990 |death_place = [[Cronulla, New South Wales]] |retired = yes |position = {{rlp|HK}} |club1 = [[Sydney University rugby league team|University]] |year1start = 1926 |year1end = 1930 |appearances1 = 62 |tries1 = 4 |goals1 = 0 |fieldgoals1 = 0 |points1 = 12 }}
'''Herbert Francis 'Frank' Benning''' [[OBE]] (1907-8 February 1990) was an Australian rugby league player and Administrator.
Frank Benning was a forward that played with the [[Sydney University rugby league team|University]] for five seasons between 1926-1930. After excelling at Rugby League he became interested in administration, and he became the club secretary of the [[Sydney University rugby league team|University]] club in 1930, a position that he retained until the club folded in 1937.<ref>Alan Whiticker/Glen Hudson: Encyclopedia of Rugby League Players. 1995 ({{ISBN|1875169571}})</ref> He was awarded an [[OBE]] in 1969 for services to the community.
Frank Benning died on 8 February 1990, aged 82.<ref>Sydney Morning Herald. Death Notice 10/2/1990</ref>
